-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Grifols, Marks & Spencer
-- 
-- Thu May 22, 2014 12:58AM EDT
-- None



May 22 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Grifols and Marks & Spencer, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Grifols <GRLS.MC>: SocGen starts with sell rating * Kloeckner & Co SE <KCOGn.DE>: Jefferies raises to buy rating * Marks & Spencer <MKS.L>: S&P Capital IQ cuts to hold from buyFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.  * Exova Group <EXO.L>: Barclays rates overweight; price target 270p  * Great Portland <GPOR.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 686p from 676p; rating hold * Grifols <GRLS.MC>: SocGen starts with sell rating * Kloeckner & Co SE <KCOGn.DE>: Jefferies raises to buy rating * Kloeckner & Co SE <KCOGn.DE>: Jefferies Raises Target Price To 13.50 Euros  * Marks & Spencer <MKS.L>: S&P Capital IQ cuts to hold from buy